HEADWORD: Misunderstanding
<hw>Mis*un`der*stand"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Mistake of
the meaning; error; misconception.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disagreement; difference of opinion; dissension;
quarrel.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Misunderstandings</xex> among friends.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

